State files an Amended Information charging count 1 - 3rd degree sexual assault, contrary to Section 940.225(3) of the Wisconsin Statutes and count 2 - 4th degree sexual assault, contrary to Section 940.225(3m) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - No contest plea.  Court accepts defendant's plea, finds him guilty but defers entry of judgment of conviction.   Court approves the Deferred Judgment Agreement and signs it.   Review 08-31-2017.   
Count 2 - No contest plea.   Convicted.  Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Maintain full-time work/job search as able;
3) Have no contact with C.D.M.;
4) Have no contact with children unless approved by agent, with the exception of his own biological children, as approved by DHS.;
5) Submit DNA sample;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is entitled to 213 days sentence credit. 
